**Galaxy Traveler 26CE** is OUT!

**Changelog:**

- After improving our Forum's security, we've radically changed the protection layers of our software too (Current licenses will be valid)

- Galaxy Traveler's **"Party Mode"** will be remembered active on next program run.

- Fixed an issue where when Licenses' domain was partially unavailable, it would've triggered an anti-piracy measure, deleting user's license files.

- Galaxy Traveler's license login form **"Submit"** button has been renamed to **"Request Gateway"** for making it more user friendly.

- **Galactic Player** window is now shorter for fitting on 1920 x 1080 125% resolutions, program will now remember last volume used on next runs.

- **Rine** now features "Repeat loop: HH:MM:SS" and "Close button should minimize the Rine window" features, it will remember user's preferences on next program run, fixed checkboxes' broken outlines.

- **Chromaflow** will now remember selected **"Translate From"** and **"Translate To"** languages on next program run.

**Rine:** https://i.imgur.com/shfw38a.png
**Galactic Player:** https://i.imgur.com/OW1cBul.png

-------------------------------

**Quick version 27 fix changelogs:**

- Added "Slow start fix" under maintenance for acknowledging Windows' IPv6 bugs.
- Added **"TurboScribe"** under **Misc > Other** and **Gemini** under **Misc > AI**.
- With **Rine** you can now add a specific date for an alarm to trigger. (I'm not updating this widget any further after this one)
- Added **.midi** extension support to **GalacticPlayer**.
- Minimum allowed Python version is now **3.11.0**.
- Every line of code referring to "Helper" __cringe role__ finally got removed.
